## Lessons learned
- CSS toolchain config files have their own module resolution path 
  (Tailwind, PostCSS, etc.). The "ESM project rules" extend to 
  config files, not just application code.
- Race-condition tests using real Postgres concurrency (Promise.all 
  with two real DB calls) caught the actual race. Mocked timing 
  would have lied.
- Pattern continues: tests pass, runtime fails, manual browser 
  verification catches it. Five times now.

